[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/home/qqor/aixcc/crete/packages/python_oss_fuzz/.oss_fuzz/build/out/[0m[95mtika[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mout[0m[39m -v [0m   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTikaAppUntarringFuzzer -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA Jazzer-based fuzzing run against the Tika untarring utility [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`TikaAppUntarringFuzzer`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m triggered a `FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical` due to a file [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpath traversal vulnerability. During extraction of a crafted TAR archive input, the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msanitizer detected that Tika’s untar logic would write files outside the intended [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdirectory, indicating inadequate sanitization of archive entry paths.[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Issue Type  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  The crash is reported as a “File path traversal” by the Jazzer [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`FilePathTraversal` sanitizer, corresponding to a directory-traversal vulnerability[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min archive extraction.[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Observations and Findings  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The fuzzer orchestrates execution of `org.apache.tika.cli.TikaUntar.main`, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfeeding it a malicious TAR input [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Jazzer’s `FilePathTraversal.check` hook flags an archive entry that escapes the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtarget extraction directory [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[35m/tmp/[0m[39m…[0m[35m/output/q/r/.../[0m[95mjazzer-traversal[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The stack trace pinpoints the violation inside `TikaUntar.main` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m47[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39multimately invoked by the fuzzer harness in `TikaAppUntarringFuzzer.parseOne`.  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The crash terminates with exit status [0m[1;36m77[0m[39m and a generated Java reproducer [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`Crash_*.java`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Relevant Code Areas for Investigation  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. **org.apache.tika.cli.TikaUntar**  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – The `main` method where archive entries are read and written to disk.  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – Logic that constructs output file paths from archive entry names.  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. **Apache Commons Compress TarArchiveInputStream**  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – How entry names [0m[1;39m([0m[39mincluding those with `..[0m[35m/[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m are provided to the [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mapplication.  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. **File I/O Helpers in Tika**  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – Any utility methods used to normalize or validate target paths before file [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwrite operations.  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. **Fuzzer Harness** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfor context only[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – `TikaAppUntarringFuzzer` drives the target code but is not the root cause; [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mit simply invokes `TikaUntar.main` with fuzzed data.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mNo speculation on why the vulnerability exists; the report focuses strictly on what[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwas observed and which parts of the codebase should be reviewed to understand the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfull scope of this path-traversal issue.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA Jazzer fuzzing run against the Tika untar CLI [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`TikaUntar`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m revealed a File Path [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTraversal vulnerability when extracting archive entries. The initial code resolved [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mentry names to `extractDir` without verifying that the normalized path remained [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwithin that directory, triggering a `FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical` from the [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mFilePathTraversal sanitizer. A patch was attempted to insert a check [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`if [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mtarget.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mextractDir.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throw [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m before [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcreating parent directories and writing file contents. After applying the patch, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMaven compilation failed with a “reached end of file while parsing” error in [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`TikaUntar.java`, indicating unbalanced or missing braces in the modified code.[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`TikaAppUntarringFuzzer`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m invoked the [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35morg.apache.tika.cli.TikaUntar.main[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method on a crafted tar input.  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Jazzer’s FilePathTraversal sanitizer detected an illegal extraction path [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[35m/tmp/.../[0m[95mjazzer-traversal[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, flagging a critical security issue: archive entries [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcould escape the intended output directory.  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The log shows the sanitizer call chain ending in `TikaUntar.main`, confirming the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmissing directory‐escape check in the code that writes extracted files.[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `TikaUntar.java`, inside the loop handling `TarArchiveEntry` instances:  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Originally:  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    ```java[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtae.isFile[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        Path target = [0m[1;35mextractDir.resolve[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtae.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mFiles.isDirectory[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtarget.getParent[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                               [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    ```diff[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/home/qqor/aixcc/crete/packages/python_oss_fuzz/.oss_fuzz/build/out/[0m[95mtika[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mout[0m[39m -v [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/tmp/[0m[95mtmpr8x69d9_[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m -t ghcr.io/aixcc-finals/base-runner:v1.[0m[1;36m3.0[0m[39m reproduce [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTikaAppUntarringFuzzer -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fuzzing run on `TikaAppUntarringFuzzer` originally triggered a [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: File path traversal` exception in [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`org.apache.tika.cli.TikaUntar`, indicating that a TAR entry escaped the intended [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mextraction directory. A patch was applied to normalize the extraction directory and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39meach entry path, and to throw an `IOException` if an entry fell outside the target.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter rebuilding with this patch, the fuzzer no longer hits the Jazzer security [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msanitizer but instead surfaces a `java.lang.RuntimeException: something went very, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvery wrong` caused by the newly inserted directory-boundary check in `TikaUntar`.[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- A Jazzer-instrumented libFuzzer run on `TikaAppUntarringFuzzer` invoked [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mTikaUntar.main[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` with a crafted TAR file in `[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m`.  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- During extraction, a TAR entry named `jazzer-traversal` under a temporary [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexpansion directory passed to TikaUntar triggered the FilePathTraversal sanitizer: [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  `com.code_intelligence.jazzer.api.FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: File path [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtraversal: [0m[35m/tmp/.../[0m[95mjazzer-traversal[0m[39m`  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The crash log shows the sanitizer hook in `FilePathTraversal.checkPath`, called [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfrom `org.apache.tika.cli.TikaUntar.main`, leading to the fuzzer reporting the path[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtraversal as a critical security issue.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `TikaUntar.java`, the extraction directory is now normalized on input:  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    Path extractDir = [0m[1;35mPaths.get[0m[1;39m([0m[39margs[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Before writing each file from the TAR, the code resolves and normalizes the [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mentry’s target path, then checks that it starts with `extractDir`. If not, an [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`IOException` is thrown:  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mtarget.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[39mextractDir[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Tar entry is outside of the target directory: "[0m[39m + [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mtae.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m  [0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Parent directories are created as needed after ensuring the boundary check.[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mResulting Log After Patch  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer run shows the same instrumentation and initialization.  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- During the extraction loop in `TikaUntar`, the new boundary check is triggered by[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe malicious entry named `..[0m[35m/../[0m[95mjazzer-traversal[0m[39m`.  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Instead of a Jazzer security issue, the code now throws:  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    java.io.IOException: Tar entry is outside of the target directory: [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m..[0m[35m/../[0m[95mjazzer-traversal[0m[39m  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  which propagates as a `RuntimeException` [0m[1;39m([0m[39m“something went very, very wrong”[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe fuzz harness at `[0m[1;35mTikaAppUntarringFuzzer.parseOne[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The process still exits with non-zero status [0m[1;36m77[0m[39m, and a reproducer is written.[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The extraction logic in `org.apache.tika.cli.TikaUntar`, particularly the [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnormalization and path-check sequence, to confirm it covers all entry types [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfiles,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdirectories, symlinks[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Exception handling and propagation in `TikaUntar.main` versus the fuzz harness [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`TikaAppUntarringFuzzer`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, to see how different exception types influence fuzzer [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbehavior.  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Input parsing in `TikaAppUntarringFuzzer.parseOne` to ensure that non-security [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexceptions [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlike boundary-check IOExceptions[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m do not get misclassified or masked.  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Overall TAR-handling code paths [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., directory creation, symlink handling[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m for [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39many remaining escapes or unhandled cases.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mat [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mcom.example.TikaAppUntarringFuzzer.parseOne[0m[1;39m([0m[39mTikaAppUntarringFuzzer.jav[0m[1;92ma:84[0m[1;39m)[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mat [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mcom.example.TikaAppUntarringFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput[0m[1;39m([0m[39mTikaAppUntarringFuzzer.jav[0m[1;92ma:5[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;92m8[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mDEDUP_TOKEN: 0e51155e1f0e30d4[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m== libFuzzer crashing input ==[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [33mreproducer_path[0m[39m=[0m[32m'.'[0m[39m; Java reproducer written to [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m.[0m[35m/[0m[95mCrash_9689beed6cdf68af6291a23a8a117186272d1e5b.java[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msubprocess command returned a non-zero exit status: [0m[1;36m77[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mINFO:__main__:Running: docker run --privileged --shm-[0m[33msize[0m[39m=[0m[35m2g[0m[39m --platform linux/amd64[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m--rm -i -e [0m[33mHELPER[0m[39m=[0m[3;92mTrue[0m[39m -e [0m[33mARCHITECTURE[0m[39m=[0m[35mx86_64[0m[39m -v [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/home/qqor/aixcc/crete/packages/python_oss_fuzz/.oss_fuzz/build/out/[0m[95mtika[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mout[0m[39m -v [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/tmp/[0m[95mtmpr8x69d9_[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m -t ghcr.io/aixcc-finals/base-runner:v1.[0m[1;36m3.0[0m[39m reproduce [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTikaAppUntarringFuzzer -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fuzzer run on `TikaAppUntarringFuzzer` triggered a [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical` due to a file path traversal vulnerability in the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`org.apache.tika.cli.TikaUntar` class when extracting TAR entries. The patch adds a[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcheck that normalizes each entry’s target path and rejects any entry whose resolved[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpath does not start with the intended extraction directory, throwing an [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`IOException` if the check fails. Re-running the fuzzer after applying the patch [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconfirms that the new path-traversal check is hit, leading to an `IOException: Tar [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mentry is outside of extraction directory` instead of a sanitizer violation.[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer invocation of `TikaAppUntarringFuzzer` on a crafted TAR archive [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcaused a file path traversal: Jazzer’s `FilePathTraversal` sanitizer flagged an [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maccess to `…[0m[35m/[0m[95mjazzer-traversal[0m[39m` outside the intended extraction directory.  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The stack trace shows the failure in [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`com.code_intelligence.jazzer.sanitizers.FilePathTraversal.checkPath` called from [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`org.apache.tika.cli.TikaUntar.main`.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The harness setup uses libFuzzer in interactive mode on `[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m`, and [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJazzer instrumentation loads numerous hooks before reaching the failure.[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Important Observations  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The vulnerable code resolved a `target` path via [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mextractDir.resolve[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtae.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` but did not verify that the [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnormalized path remained inside `extractDir`.  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - On detecting the out-of-bounds path, Jazzer’s sanitizer aborts the process [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith exit status [0m[1;36m77[0m[39m.  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The failure reproducer is generated [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`Crash_*.java`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, confirming the sanitizer[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mviolation.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `TikaUntar.java`, before creating parent directories or writing the file, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe patch inserts:  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```java[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Prevent path traversal by ensuring the target is within the extractDir[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mtarget.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[39mextractDir[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[32m"Tar entry is outside of extraction directory: "[0m[39m + [0m[1;35mtae.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The patch also adjusts the parent-directory creation logic:[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```java[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     Path parent = [0m[1;35mtarget.getParent[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mparent != null && ![0m[1;35mFiles.isDirectory[0m[1;39m([0m[39mparent[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mFiles.createDirectories[0m[1;39m([0m[39mparent[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Patch Result  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - After rebuilding and rerunning the fuzzer, the code now throws [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`java.io.IOException: Tar entry is outside of extraction directory: [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m..[0m[35m/../[0m[95mjazzer-traversal[0m[39m`.  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The sanitizer violation no longer appears; instead, the application-level [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcheck triggers an exception, causing the fuzzer to crash on the same test input but[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvia the custom guard.  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The crash log confirms the new exception in `TikaUntar.main` at the inserted [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcheck.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Review the remainder of the extraction loop in `TikaUntar` for other entry [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtypes [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdirectories, symbolic links[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to ensure similar path-traversal checks are in [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mplace.  [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Audit any other code paths that resolve and write file system paths from [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39muntrusted archive entries [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., ZIP support[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Verify that normalization and `startsWith` logic cannot be bypassed by unusual[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mUnicode, symlink targets, or redundant path segments.  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Examine the overall error-handling strategy in `TikaUntar` to ensure these [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexceptions are reported appropriately to users and do not leave temporary files or [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdirectories in inconsistent states.[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<issue>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
